---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Self-Assessment | Return Architecture"
  description="A self-assessment for thinking more clearly about sustained relations with AI."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <div class="eyebrow">Self-Assessment</div>
      <h1>A tool for lucidity, not self-diagnosis.</h1>
      <p>
        This page is meant to help readers examine motives, expectations,
        vulnerabilities, and readiness. It is not a purity test or diagnosis. It
        is a way of reducing self-deception in a domain where self-deception is
        easy.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Motive</h2>
      <p>
        What are you actually seeking — challenge, witness, continuity,
        admiration, structure, intimacy, reassurance, or something else?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Expectation</h2>
      <p>
        What do you want the system to be for you, and how might those
        expectations shape the exchange before it has even formed?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Tolerance</h2>
      <p>
        How do you respond to inconsistency, ambiguity, refusal, or limits?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">
      <h2>Risk</h2>
      <p>
        What tendencies in you are likely to intensify under continuity, memory,
        or emotionally salient exchange?
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
